  {
    "client_msg_id": "cff689d8-9b61-4e67-b135-d935cb8f9f69",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "In practice people learn languages symbolically regardless, whether the syntax is \"field of button\" or \"button.field\" – \n\nWhen I was 12, knowing hypertalk's `\"send message 'abc' to card 'foo'\"` and then encountering C's `foo-&gt;abc()` , it clicked immediately and my reaction was \"cool!\" – so for me at least it worked\n\nParsing is the hyperscript programmer's problem, keeping a sane grammar – and others can probably hack around that grammar for a less talky syntax in the future",
    "user": "USH01JEDQ",
    "ts": "1615922963.001600",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "g0c975eeefb0",
      "image_72": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0c975eeefb0d9484d0ccce64bbd16e85.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0012-72.png",
      "first_name": "Christopher",
      "real_name": "Christopher Galtenberg",
      "display_name": "Chris G",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "galtenberg",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "blocks": [
      {
