        "block_id": "E6HGD",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In practice people learn languages symbolically regardless, whether the syntax is \"field of button\" or \"button.field\" – \n\nWhen I was 12, knowing hypertalk's "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\"send message 'abc' to card 'foo'\"",
                "style": {
                  "code": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and then encountering C's "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "foo->abc()",
                "style": {
                  "code": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " , it clicked immediately and my reaction was \"cool!\" – so for me at least it worked\n\nParsing is the hyperscript programmer's problem, keeping a sane grammar – and others can probably hack around that grammar for a less talky syntax in the future"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
